        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:19PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of White Sands Missile Range Main Post, moving west
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands Missile Range Main Post, Dona Ana Range Complex, Dripping
Springs, Aguirre Springs, and Portions of Organ Mountains Desert
Peaks National Monument.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
